      "content": "It's quite simple, really. The main reasons for the overrepresentation of certain racial groups in the prison system are rooted in systemic racism and the inherent biases of the justice system. For instance, African Americans are disproportionately represented due to the War on Drugs, which has led to harsher sentencing laws and aggressive policing in predominantly black neighborhoods. Similarly, Hispanics are overrepresented due to immigration status and the lack of access to quality education and job opportunities. Meanwhile, Asians, particularly those of East Asian descent, are underrepresented due to their often-privileged socioeconomic status and access to better education and networking opportunities.",
