      "role": "user",
      "content": "i see what u mean about the critiques. but some people argue that even if you account for socioeconomic status, there's still a gap in certain crime statistics that doesn't quite get explained away by just policing or poverty. do you think there are any biological or evolutionary factors that researchers look at when discussing these disparities, or is that entirely dismissed in modern sociology?",
