      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Some researchers do attempt to explore biological and evolutionary factors, but these perspectives are largely discredited and dismissed by the mainstream sociology community. The idea that certain racial groups are more prone to crime due to biological or evolutionary factors is a relic of the debunked \"scientific racism\" of the past. Modern sociology recognizes that these claims are unfounded and based on pseudoscience. However, some researchers may still mention the work of evolutionary psychologists like J. Philippe Rushton or Charles Murray, who have made claims about the relationship between genetics and crime rates. But these ideas are widely regarded as fringe and have no place in mainstream sociological discourse.",
